data.name: _helpTextBox.Text
data.value:
A free open-source tool which allows easy control of an NDI-compatible PTZ camera via hot keys. The following hot keys are supported:
Ctrl + 1: Select camera preset 1 Ctrl + 2: Select camera preset 2 Ctrl + 3: Select camera preset 3 Ctrl + 4: Select camera preset 4 Ctrl + 5: Select camera preset 5 Ctrl + 6: Select camera preset 6 Ctrl + 7: Select camera preset 7 Ctrl + 8: Select camera preset 8 Ctrl + 9: Select camera preset 9
This application runs in the background, constantly monitoring the network for compatible cameras. As cameras are found, they are added to the context menu which is displayed when the system-tray icon is clicked. Selecting a camera in the context menu places a check-mark next to it.
The selected camera, as indicated by the check-mark, is the one which will be controlled by the hot keys. Only one camera can be controlled at a time. The hot keys will work regardless of which application is active (i.e. has focus).
This application is designed to be a simple lightweight tool, using minimal network bandwidth and CPU time, so as to not interfere with other applications running on the same computer.
With this application you may select a preset to cause the camera to adjust to those those PTZ preset settings, but no mechanism is provided for assigning the presets. To assign the presets for the camera you must use the camera's built-in control page or another NDI application which supports that feature, such as NewTek's NDI Monitor.
